  "final_answer": "Honey is a traditional ingredient that has been linked to curing fever, with key compounds including glucose, fructose, and polyphenols. The main ingredients and their corresponding compounds are: \n- Honey, with its key compounds glucose and fructose, \n- Honey also contains polyphenols. \nAccording to a Hadith, the Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him) said, \"Fever is from the heat of the (Hell) Fire, so cool it with water,\" as narrated by Aisha, and also mentioned by Ibn Abbas, who advised to \"Cool your fever with Zamzam water.\" The reference for this Hadith can be found in Bukhari: 3261; Book. 59; English vol. 4; Book. 54; Hadees. 483 and Bukhari: 3263; Book. 59; English vol. 4; Book. 54; Hadees. 485.\nIt is essential to consult a healthcare professional before using any traditional or natural ingredients for medicinal purposes, as they may interact with other medications or have side effects.",
